Taiga is an open-source project management tool designed for agile development teams. It supports various methodologies, including Scrum, Kanban, and hybrid approaches, making it ideal for managing tasks, sprints, backlogs, and issues. Taiga offers features such as user stories, bug tracking, task management, and real-time collaboration, all within a customizable and user-friendly interface. It integrates with popular tools like GitHub, GitLab, and Slack, and can be self-hosted or used via its cloud service.
